DIGEST
SB 272 Original 2026 Regular Session Bass
Present law authorizes the secretary of DEQ to create a program to expedite processing of
permits, modifications, licenses, registrations, and variances and to adopt rules for such a
program. Further authorizes the secretary to create a federal permitting parity program to
expedite processing of permits, modifications, registrations, and variances for nuclear power
generation.
Proposed law retains present law and directs the secretary to adopt rules to provide notice
that a permit issued under present law is being issued pursuant to the federal permitting
parity program for nuclear power.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 30:2014.5(B)(2))
